### CityVoice – Auth API Tests
### Compatible with: IntelliJ HTTP Client, VS Code REST Client
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080/api

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@adminEmail = admin@cityvoice.vn
@adminPassword = Admin@123
@citizenEmail = finnzxje@gmail.com
@citizenPassword = Test@12345


# ─── 1. STAFF / ADMIN LOGIN ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1a. Successful staff login (saves tokens globally)
# @name adminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/staff/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{adminPassword}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.data.accessToken);
  client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.data.refreshToken);
  client.test("Login OK", () => client.assert(response.status === 200));
  client.test("Has accessToken", () => client.assert(response.body.data.accessToken !== ""));
%}

###

### 1b. Wrong password – expect 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/staff/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}


# ─── 2. CURRENT USER ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 2a. GET /me (requires valid Bearer token from step 1a)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 2b. GET /me without token – expect 403
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me


# ─── 3. TOKEN REFRESH + LOGOUT ───────────────────────────────────────────────

### 3a. Refresh access token (rotates refresh token)
# @name tokenRefresh
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.data.accessToken);
  client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.data.refreshToken);
%}

###

### 3b. Logout (revokes the current refresh token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### 3c. Refresh with revoked token – expect 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}


# ─── 4. CITIZEN REGISTRATION FLOW ───────────────────────────────────────────

### 4a. Register new citizen (sends verification OTP email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/citizen/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{citizenEmail}}",
  "password": "{{citizenPassword}}",
  "fullName": "Nguyen Van A",
  "phoneNumber": "0901234567"
}

###

### 4b. Resend verification OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/citizen/resend-verification
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{citizenEmail}}"
}

###

### 4c. Verify email OTP (replace 123456 with actual OTP from email)
# @name verifyEmail
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/citizen/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{citizenEmail}}",
  "otp": "123456"
}

###

### 4d. Register duplicate email – expect 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/citizen/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{citizenEmail}}",
  "password": "{{citizenPassword}}",
  "fullName": "Duplicate User"
}


# ─── 5. CITIZEN LOGIN ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 5a. Citizen login with password
# @name citizenPasswordLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/citizen/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{citizenEmail}}",
  "password": "{{citizenPassword}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("citizenAccessToken", response.body.data.accessToken);
  client.global.set("citizenRefreshToken", response.body.data.refreshToken);
%}

###

### 5b. Citizen login before verification – expect 403
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/citizen/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "unverified@example.com",
  "password": "Test@12345"
}

###

### 5c. Request OTP login code
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/citizen/request-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{citizenEmail}}"
}

###

### 5d. Login with OTP (replace 654321 with actual OTP from email)
# @name citizenOtpLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/citizen/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{citizenEmail}}",
  "otp": "654321"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("citizenAccessToken", response.body.data.accessToken);
%}

###

### 5e. GET /me as citizen
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenAccessToken}}

###

### 5f. Citizen using staff login endpoint – expect 403
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/staff/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{citizenEmail}}",
  "password": "{{citizenPassword}}"
}
